243
00:11:54,250 --> 00:11:56,291
But like I was saying, I'll
just have to kick your butt

244
00:11:56,375 --> 00:11:57,625
the old fashioned way.

245
00:11:57,708 --> 00:11:59,333
[LEADER] For your hubris,
and your crimes,

246
00:11:59,416 --> 00:12:02,000
you will pay with your head.

247
00:12:02,083 --> 00:12:03,958
[NATSU] Listen pal, I've had
more than my fair share

248
00:12:04,041 --> 00:12:05,833
of fights where I
didn't use magic.

249
00:12:05,916 --> 00:12:07,791
So I ain't scared
of you at all.

250
00:12:07,875 --> 00:12:10,083
I'm not gonna
lose to a guy like you.

251
00:12:10,166 --> 00:12:11,458
'Cause I've got some
other scores to settle

252
00:12:11,541 --> 00:12:13,041
when we're done here.

253
00:12:13,125 --> 00:12:15,166
[LEADER] You guild wizards
are ridiculous.

254
00:12:15,250 --> 00:12:16,833
I won't deny that
you're strong...

255
00:12:16,916 --> 00:12:20,250
But you will still fall before
me like all the other criminals!

256
00:12:20,333 --> 00:12:23,583
And like them, you'll
become a nameless corpse!

257
00:12:23,666 --> 00:12:25,000
[NATSU] I don't think so!

258
00:12:25,083 --> 00:12:28,250
Gimme a shot! 'Cause
I'm fired up now!

259
00:12:46,458 --> 00:12:48,375
I wish we could
help Natsu and them.

260
00:12:48,458 --> 00:12:51,416
but master told us that we
shouldn't leave the coliseum.

261
00:12:51,500 --> 00:12:52,750
Well, he's
right about that.

262
00:12:52,833 --> 00:12:55,208
We don't wanna attract
any unwarranted attention.

263
00:12:55,291 --> 00:12:56,500
If someone gets
suspicious it could

264
00:12:56,583 --> 00:12:59,750
put Lucy's rescue
mission in trouble.

265
00:12:59,833 --> 00:13:00,750
Oh, hey.

266
00:13:00,833 --> 00:13:02,291
You ladies run off
to grab a snack?

267
00:13:02,375 --> 00:13:04,625
[KINANA] Yeah, and walk
off some nerves, too.

268
00:13:04,708 --> 00:13:05,666
[MAX] Tell me about it.

269
00:13:05,750 --> 00:13:07,333
I'm worried about
Natsu and Lucy.

270
00:13:07,416 --> 00:13:09,583
And the games are making
me even more stressed out.

271
00:13:09,666 --> 00:13:10,708
[LAKI] Where'd Warren go?

272
00:13:10,791 --> 00:13:13,041
I haven't seen him
in a little while.

273
00:13:13,125 --> 00:13:15,750
[MAX] Somethin' was gettin'
in the way of his telepathy...

274
00:13:15,833 --> 00:13:17,458
So he was gonna try to
get up onto higher ground

275
00:13:17,541 --> 00:13:19,166
to see if that helps.

276
00:13:19,250 --> 00:13:21,583
[KINANA] I'd love to get
outta here, but we can't...

277
00:13:21,666 --> 00:13:23,875
It feels so helpless,
just waiting.

278
00:13:23,958 --> 00:13:26,000
[LAKI] It'll work out.
You know Natsu...

279
00:13:26,083 --> 00:13:28,875
I'll bet he's probably on
his way back with Lucy.

280
00:13:28,958 --> 00:13:30,666
And the match seems
to be going our way,

281
00:13:30,750 --> 00:13:32,916
exactly like Master Mavis
said that it would.

282
00:13:33,000 --> 00:13:35,541
But there still are a lot
of tough ones left to beat.

283
00:13:35,625 --> 00:13:37,291
Just have faith in her plan
and we'll win the games,

284
00:13:37,375 --> 00:13:39,541
and have everybody
back to celebrate.

285
00:13:39,625 --> 00:13:41,291
[ELFMAN] I'm a man!

286
00:13:41,375 --> 00:13:42,833
[MAX] Yeah, nobody
said that you weren't!

287
00:13:42,916 --> 00:13:44,375
Help me talk
some sense into him!

288
00:13:44,458 --> 00:13:46,208
I'm making
perfect sense.

289
00:13:46,291 --> 00:13:47,583
What's the matter?

290
00:13:47,666 --> 00:13:49,708
Mira went with the team
that was going after Lucy..

291
00:13:49,791 --> 00:13:51,916
We shoulda heard something
from them by now!

292
00:13:52,000 --> 00:13:54,250
So, this genius thinks
that we all need to go

293
00:13:54,333 --> 00:13:57,583
off and storm the royal palace
so we can go help them fight!

294
00:13:57,666 --> 00:13:59,000
[MAX] Not exactly the best idea.

295
00:13:59,083 --> 00:14:00,750
[ELFMAN] I know Mira can
hold her own but I'm worried,

296
00:14:00,833 --> 00:14:02,750
and a real man fights
to save his family.

297
00:14:02,833 --> 00:14:04,250
[LISANNA] We all want to help
them, but we just have to

298
00:14:04,333 --> 00:14:06,625
give it some time
for the plan to work!

299
00:14:06,708 --> 00:14:08,041
Got no other choice.

300
00:14:08,125 --> 00:14:09,708
Besides, she's with Natsu
and he won't let anything

301
00:14:09,791 --> 00:14:11,000
bad happen to her.

302
00:14:11,083 --> 00:14:13,291
Well. As long as he
doesn't do something crazy

303
00:14:13,375 --> 00:14:17,791
and stray away
from the plan.

304
00:14:17,875 --> 00:14:19,375
That's it! I'm going!

305
00:14:19,458 --> 00:14:21,250
No, you're not!

306
00:14:21,333 --> 00:14:22,916
Just try to relax, man...

307
00:14:23,000 --> 00:14:25,250
Natsu went through that whole
"second origin" thing...

308
00:14:25,333 --> 00:14:26,625
And we all just saw
him beat the crap

309
00:14:26,708 --> 00:14:28,583
out of those guys
from Sabertooth.

310
00:14:28,666 --> 00:14:30,708
Mirajane has
her Satan Soul forms,

311
00:14:30,791 --> 00:14:32,708
and Wendy is a
Dragon Slayer, too...

312
00:14:32,791 --> 00:14:34,208
We'd just get in their way.

313
00:14:34,291 --> 00:14:35,500
You're absolutely right.

314
00:14:35,583 --> 00:14:37,250
We should focus our
energy on our team spirit

315
00:14:37,333 --> 00:14:40,333
and cheer for our
guys in the match.

316
00:14:40,416 --> 00:14:42,500
All right... I guess
I could pound some sense

317
00:14:42,583 --> 00:14:44,458
into that old geezer
Darton, instead.

318
00:14:44,541 --> 00:14:45,791
Were you
even listening?

319
00:14:45,875 --> 00:14:47,041
You're staying with us!

320
00:14:47,125 --> 00:14:48,750
We should probably
get back to our seats...

321
00:14:48,833 --> 00:14:51,125
Somebody could be
watching us right now.

322
00:14:51,208 --> 00:14:54,083
You're right. Come
on, let's get moving.

323
00:14:54,166 --> 00:14:57,375
[ELFMAN] Yeah, okay... But
I still don't like this.

324
00:14:57,458 --> 00:14:58,833
A real man would do
something, ya know?

325
00:14:58,916 --> 00:15:00,666
I know, but
that's how it is.

326
00:15:00,750 --> 00:15:02,541
Mirajane can handle it.

327
00:15:02,625 --> 00:15:04,166
Actually the
real truth is...

328
00:15:04,250 --> 00:15:07,208
we should feel sorry for the
poor soul who tries to stop her.

329
00:15:09,750 --> 00:15:12,125
Impossible. You should
be so full of poison by now

330
00:15:12,208 --> 00:15:15,416
that your body feels like it's
burning from the inside out!

331
00:15:15,500 --> 00:15:17,125
You should
be on your knees.

332
00:15:17,208 --> 00:15:18,625
screaming in pain

333
00:15:18,708 --> 00:15:20,708
and begging me to put
you out of your misery!

334
00:15:20,791 --> 00:15:23,833
How in the hell can
you still be standing up?!

335
00:15:24,458 --> 00:15:25,791
[MIRAJANE] That's easy.

336
00:15:25,875 --> 00:15:28,541
There are so many things
that you don't know about me.

337
00:15:28,625 --> 00:15:30,541
Like, when I know
that I'm being watched...

338
00:15:30,625 --> 00:15:32,500
or anywhere around
people, really.

339
00:15:32,583 --> 00:15:34,125
I tend to stay a little guarded.

340
00:15:34,208 --> 00:15:35,916
I try not to go all
out strength-wise,

341
00:15:36,000 --> 00:15:38,041
because I don't
wanna scare anybody.

342
00:15:38,125 --> 00:15:39,250
What?

343
00:15:39,333 --> 00:15:40,333
[MIRAJANE] It's funny.

344
00:15:40,416 --> 00:15:42,500
I'm a walking
contradiction, I guess.

345
00:15:42,583 --> 00:15:46,708
But it's just the way I am.
Always have been.

346
00:15:46,791 --> 00:15:48,500
But whenever it's just me,

347
00:15:48,583 --> 00:15:50,750
I can go full-throttle
one hundred percent

348
00:15:50,833 --> 00:15:53,083
power, no
problem at all.

349
00:15:53,166 --> 00:15:56,000
What exactly are
you trying to say?

350
00:15:56,083 --> 00:15:57,458
[KAMIKA gasps]

351
00:15:58,916 --> 00:16:02,875
[KAMIKA] Unbelievable!
Is she really inhaling it?!

352
00:16:04,125 --> 00:16:05,333
[MIRAJANE chuckles]

353
00:16:05,416 --> 00:16:09,416
[MIRAJANE] Demons
like me love poison.

354
00:16:09,500 --> 00:16:12,125
It's actually one of
my very favorite things.

355
00:16:12,208 --> 00:16:13,875
A disgusting
Take-Over spell...

356
00:16:13,958 --> 00:16:17,166
But I suppose it's fitting for
a filthy criminal like you!

357
00:16:17,250 --> 00:16:18,375
It's over!

358
00:16:18,458 --> 00:16:20,958
Because I can still
leave you paralyzed!

359
00:16:23,458 --> 00:16:27,208
[KAMIKA] The gray papers
hold the spirit of protection!

360
00:16:27,291 --> 00:16:28,875
[MIRAJANE] You may
be an executioner...

361
00:16:28,958 --> 00:16:30,833
but just how much
of a fighter are you

362
00:16:30,916 --> 00:16:32,500
when your victim
can fight back?!

363
00:16:33,708 --> 00:16:37,000
[KAMIKA] The blue papers hold
the spirit of divine winds!

364
00:16:37,083 --> 00:16:40,791
[MIRAJANE] Oh? The "divine"
running away from the demonic?

365
00:16:40,875 --> 00:16:42,250
Not this time.

366
00:16:42,875 --> 00:16:44,250
[KAMIKA] She can fly?!

367
00:16:45,000 --> 00:16:47,000
[MIRAJANE] I'll ask
you once again!

368
00:16:47,083 --> 00:16:49,958
[KAMIKA grunts]

369
00:16:50,041 --> 00:16:51,708
[MIRAJANE] Can you tell
me where my friends went

370
00:16:51,791 --> 00:16:53,708
or is this gonna get ugly?

371
00:16:56,791 --> 00:16:58,375
[KAMIKA coughing]

372
00:16:58,458 --> 00:17:01,291
I don't have to tell you
anything I don't want to!

373
00:17:01,375 --> 00:17:02,625
[MIRAJANE] How far
are you willing to go

374
00:17:02,708 --> 00:17:04,666
to keep it from me?!

375
00:17:04,750 --> 00:17:05,958
Because, I'm
ready to fight you

376
00:17:06,041 --> 00:17:07,333
without holding anything back...

377
00:17:07,416 --> 00:17:09,583
So you'd better give me
the answer I'm looking for.

378
00:17:09,666 --> 00:17:11,541
You're an
unclean monster!

379
00:17:11,625 --> 00:17:13,250
[MIRAJANE] I'm a She-devil!

380
00:17:16,041 --> 00:17:18,541
[KAMIKA] The black papers
hold the spirit of cleansing!

381
00:17:18,625 --> 00:17:19,708
I can defeat a devil!

382
00:17:19,791 --> 00:17:22,583
All I have to do is
purge your darkness!

383
00:17:22,666 --> 00:17:24,708
[KAMIKA gasps]

384
00:17:24,791 --> 00:17:27,791
My darkness is a flame
that'll never go out!

385
00:17:27,875 --> 00:17:29,166
She's gone!

386
00:17:29,250 --> 00:17:31,458
[KAMIKA grunts]

387
00:17:31,541 --> 00:17:33,833
[KAMIKA] The indigo papers
hold the spirit of love.

388
00:17:33,916 --> 00:17:34,958
Meaning they'll
conjure up any pain

389
00:17:35,041 --> 00:17:36,916
you've endured
grieving over love!

390
00:17:37,000 --> 00:17:39,375
And your heart will
literally be broken!

391
00:17:40,916 --> 00:17:42,166
[roaring]

392
00:17:42,250 --> 00:17:46,791
[LISANNA] C'mon.
Don't be afraid, Big Brother.

393
00:17:46,875 --> 00:17:47,458
We still love you.

394
00:17:47,541 --> 00:17:48,458
[MIRAJANE] Lisanna!

395
00:17:48,541 --> 00:17:51,250
You have to wake up, Lisanna!

396
00:17:51,333 --> 00:17:59,458
[rain pouring]

397
00:17:59,541 --> 00:18:01,458
[KAMIKA] Now you'll be
trapped in your misery.

398
00:18:01,541 --> 00:18:03,291
Forced to relive the trauma
and go through the pain

399
00:18:03,375 --> 00:18:06,166
over and over again.
An endless hell.

400
00:18:06,250 --> 00:18:07,416
The grief will
keep intensifying

401
00:18:07,500 --> 00:18:08,958
until you lose your mind.

402
00:18:09,041 --> 00:18:10,416
Ah...

403
00:18:12,083 --> 00:18:15,458
[MIRAJANE] I got over
that pain a long time ago...

404
00:18:15,541 --> 00:18:19,250
I know that I'm one of the
lucky ones, but I'm not alone...

405
00:18:19,333 --> 00:18:21,458
Everyone experiences
profound pain

406
00:18:21,541 --> 00:18:23,291
at some point
in their life.

407
00:18:23,375 --> 00:18:25,000
But they
can all heal.

408
00:18:25,083 --> 00:18:27,375
Let the past fade
into their memory.

409
00:18:27,458 --> 00:18:29,625
For me, magic
gives me the strength

410
00:18:29,708 --> 00:18:31,041
I need to grow from it.

411
00:18:31,125 --> 00:18:32,416
Stop all this babbling!

412
00:18:32,500 --> 00:18:34,208
I won't be lectured
by a criminal like--

413
00:18:34,291 --> 00:18:35,958
[KAMIKA muffled screams]

414
00:18:36,041 --> 00:18:37,208
[MIRAJANE] I learned
how to use my power

415
00:18:37,291 --> 00:18:39,708
to protect the
people I care about.

416
00:18:39,791 --> 00:18:40,916
Let me show you.

417
00:18:41,000 --> 00:18:42,958
[KAMIKA whimpers]

418
00:18:43,041 --> 00:18:44,250
[LUCY wails]

419
00:18:44,333 --> 00:18:46,291
This water is boiling!

420
00:18:46,375 --> 00:18:48,583
That means Aquarius
can't use it to attack.

421
00:18:48,666 --> 00:18:50,916
What are we gonna do?

422
00:18:51,000 --> 00:18:52,458
[UOSUKE] Yeah, she's
right on the money.

423
00:18:52,541 --> 00:18:55,208
So, why don't ya haul it on
outta here, ya old rotten fish!

424
00:18:55,291 --> 00:18:56,875
You're all used up,
and I guarantee

425
00:18:56,958 --> 00:18:59,625
if I was your boyfriend,
I woulda thrown ya back too!

426
00:18:59,708 --> 00:19:01,500
[LUCY] What a low blow!

427
00:19:02,041 --> 00:19:03,250
What?!

428
00:19:03,333 --> 00:19:04,916
I don't think he
shoulda said all that!

429
00:19:05,000 --> 00:19:06,750
Definitely not.

430
00:19:06,833 --> 00:19:08,625
[AQUARIUS] Water temperature
doesn't make a bit of difference

431
00:19:08,708 --> 00:19:10,791
to me. This idiot
even summoned me

432
00:19:10,875 --> 00:19:12,666
in the middle of
her bath before.

433
00:19:12,750 --> 00:19:13,833
Huh?

434
00:19:13,916 --> 00:19:15,666
Oh, yeah. That was
not such a good time.

435
00:19:15,750 --> 00:19:17,333
Kinda blocked it out.

436
00:19:17,416 --> 00:19:18,583
[UOSUKE] I was sure
that was gonna work!

437
00:19:18,666 --> 00:19:19,791
What a load of chum!

438
00:19:19,875 --> 00:19:22,000
[LUCY] Now, let's teach
this jerk a lesson!

439
00:19:22,083 --> 00:19:23,750
Why don't
we just kill him?!

440
00:19:25,166 --> 00:19:26,791
[PANTHERLILY grunts]

441
00:19:26,875 --> 00:19:28,333
[NEPPA] You got popped!

442
00:19:28,416 --> 00:19:30,000
There's never been a criminal
that's been able to get away

443
00:19:30,083 --> 00:19:34,083
from my Multi-Angle acid
technique, so say your prayers!

444
00:19:34,166 --> 00:19:35,541
[PANTHERLILY] Dig deep...

445
00:19:35,625 --> 00:19:38,083
I won't be able to stay in
combat mode for much longer.

446
00:19:38,166 --> 00:19:39,833
Gotta
make it count!

447
00:19:39,916 --> 00:19:41,750
[GAJEEL] Come on! Is
that all ya got!

448
00:19:41,833 --> 00:19:43,875
Step it up!

449
00:19:43,958 --> 00:19:45,125
[PANTHERLILY thinking]
All those days I spent

450
00:19:45,208 --> 00:19:47,916
training with Gajeel.
I gotta remember them.

451
00:19:48,000 --> 00:19:49,500
[grunting]

452
00:19:49,583 --> 00:19:53,583
[GAJEEL] Don't get soft on me!
Hit me with your best shot! Now!

453
00:19:53,666 --> 00:19:55,958
[NEPPA] Eh?

454
00:19:56,041 --> 00:19:57,791
[PANTHERLILY] No matter how
many times he pummeled me

455
00:19:57,875 --> 00:20:00,750
with those iron fists,
I never gave up!

456
00:20:03,666 --> 00:20:05,250
[GAJEEL yells]

457
00:20:08,416 --> 00:20:10,541
Hey. Tell me something...

458
00:20:10,625 --> 00:20:11,708
[GAJEEL] What?

459
00:20:11,791 --> 00:20:13,625
Can you explain to
me what just happened?

460
00:20:13,708 --> 00:20:15,416
My sword is made from
metal like your body,

461
00:20:15,500 --> 00:20:17,125
so why did it
shatter to pieces?

462
00:20:17,208 --> 00:20:18,916
Isn't it obvious?

463
00:20:19,000 --> 00:20:21,458
This makes all
the difference, pal.

464
00:20:21,541 --> 00:20:24,250
Well, that and what
I got on the inside...

465
00:20:24,333 --> 00:20:27,291
There's iron in my soul.

466
00:20:27,375 --> 00:20:29,500
My mind and body
are stronger than steel!

467
00:20:29,583 --> 00:20:32,125
All your acid will
never eat that away!

468
00:20:32,208 --> 00:20:34,125
[NEPPA] Sploosh!

469
00:20:34,208 --> 00:20:36,500
And it'll never
break my spirit!

470
00:20:36,583 --> 00:20:38,666
That's the strongest of all!

471
00:20:38,750 --> 00:20:42,000
[NEPPA] Uh oh. He cut the acid?!

472
00:20:42,083 --> 00:20:43,500
[COSMOS grunts]

473
00:20:43,583 --> 00:20:47,041
[COSMOS] No! You blew away
all of my lovely spore bombs!

474
00:20:47,125 --> 00:20:50,083
But still, I have many
beautifully deadly plants

475
00:20:50,166 --> 00:20:52,125
at my disposal.

476
00:20:52,208 --> 00:20:54,958
[WENDY] What now? I gotta think.

477
00:20:55,041 --> 00:20:56,708
Even though I don't
understand her magic.

478
00:20:56,791 --> 00:20:58,000
I can't lose.

479
00:20:58,083 --> 00:21:01,000
What would
Natsu do to win?

480
00:21:01,083 --> 00:21:02,333
Yeah, definitely.

481
00:21:02,416 --> 00:21:04,375
That's exactly
what he would do.

482
00:21:05,750 --> 00:21:06,958
[LEADER] Damn you!

483
00:21:07,041 --> 00:21:09,541
I don't understand!
How can you even touch me?

484
00:21:09,625 --> 00:21:11,125
Are you some kind of monster?!

485
00:21:11,208 --> 00:21:13,291
[NATSU] Sorry,
I'm not a monster...

486
00:21:13,375 --> 00:21:16,208
But I am a Fire Dragon Slayer.

487
00:21:19,250 --> 00:21:20,625
[LEADER] No!

488
00:21:20,708 --> 00:21:23,208
[NATSU] I think you're way
overdue for a beat-down!

489
00:21:23,291 --> 00:21:25,166
[LEADER] Where is all this
strength coming from?!

490
00:21:25,250 --> 00:21:28,125
How can he still have
so much magic power?!

491
00:21:28,208 --> 00:21:29,375
[grunts]

492
00:21:29,458 --> 00:21:31,333
Did you seriously think
you could take it away?

493
00:21:31,416 --> 00:21:32,791
Think again!

494
00:21:35,916 --> 00:21:37,291
[LEADER] How dare you.

495
00:21:37,375 --> 00:21:38,708
With that, you've
truly made yourself

496
00:21:38,791 --> 00:21:40,541
an enemy of the kingdom!

497
00:21:40,625 --> 00:21:43,125
[NATSU] You know, I'm not
too worried about that...

498
00:21:43,208 --> 00:21:44,541
You should be, though.

499
00:21:44,625 --> 00:21:46,791
Because it's an even bigger
mistake to make yourself

500
00:21:46,875 --> 00:21:49,625
an enemy of the
Fairy Tail guild.

501
00:21:49,708 --> 00:21:51,041
[gasps]

502
00:21:51,125 --> 00:21:52,750
[UOSUKE yelling]

503
00:21:53,958 --> 00:21:56,291
[NATSU] And that
means everybody in it.

504
00:21:56,375 --> 00:21:58,125
[NEPPA yelling]

505
00:21:58,208 --> 00:21:59,291
We're not scared
of the kingdom

506
00:21:59,375 --> 00:22:01,375
or anybody who tries
to bring us down!

507
00:22:01,458 --> 00:22:03,708
[WENDY] Shattering Light:
Sky Drill!

508
00:22:03,791 --> 00:22:05,041
[MIRAJANE] Hyaah!

509
00:22:05,125 --> 00:22:07,583
[NATSU] We never
give up the fight!

510
00:22:11,666 --> 00:22:13,208
[ALL groaning]

511
00:22:14,125 --> 00:22:15,500
Oh!

512
00:22:15,583 --> 00:22:16,500
Nice.

513
00:22:16,583 --> 00:22:17,541
Oh, hi!

514
00:22:17,625 --> 00:22:19,083
[HAPPY] Natsu!

515
00:22:19,166 --> 00:22:20,458
[WENDY] Wow, you're all here!

516
00:22:20,541 --> 00:22:22,666
[LUCY] Talk about
perfect timing!

517
00:22:22,750 --> 00:22:24,750
Yeah, this is
totally awesome!

518
00:22:24,833 --> 00:22:25,833
[MIRAJANE] I'll say!

519
00:22:25,916 --> 00:22:27,791
And it looks like
everybody's okay!

520
00:22:27,875 --> 00:22:29,458
By the skin
of our teeth...

521
00:22:29,541 --> 00:22:31,375
And we're gonna be even
better once we figure a way

522
00:22:31,458 --> 00:22:33,083
to get out of this dungeon.

523
00:22:33,166 --> 00:22:35,708
We lost... But how?

524
00:22:35,791 --> 00:22:37,208
[NATSU] Okay, scumbag!

525
00:22:37,291 --> 00:22:40,083
Tell us where the exit is, or
you're gonna get executed.

526
00:22:40,166 --> 00:22:41,541
He's scary.

527
00:24:13,583 --> 00:24:15,500
[NATSU] Ugh. Well,
that took forever,

528
00:24:15,583 --> 00:24:18,416
but I think I finally
see sweet daylight again!

529
00:24:18,500 --> 00:24:19,333
[HAPPY] I was worried
we wouldn't make it

530
00:24:19,416 --> 00:24:20,708
past those creeps.

531
00:24:20,791 --> 00:24:22,416
[NATSU] We always do,
little buddy!

532
00:24:22,500 --> 00:24:24,666
Hold on, who's that
standing by the exit?

533
00:24:24,750 --> 00:24:26,333
Don't you think they
look kinda familiar?

534
00:24:26,416 --> 00:24:28,083
[HAPPY] Yeah, weird...

535
00:24:28,166 --> 00:24:31,375
I was just thinkin'
the exact same thing!

536
00:24:31,458 --> 00:24:33,916
[HAPPY &amp; NATSU] Next time:
The Kingdom 'til Tomorrow!

537
00:24:34,000 --> 00:24:37,791
[NATSU] Wait a second... Whoa.
I totally know that smell!

538
00:24:37,875 --> 00:24:38,791
[HAPPY] Huh?

539
00:24:38,875 --> 00:24:41,458
What in the heck
is going on here?!

